{"lemma": "سِكَّةٌ", "slug": "سِكَّةٌ", "root": "س.ك.ك", "root_slug": "س-ك-ك", "root_link": "/words/roots/س-ك-ك", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 2, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 6}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n20161"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%90%D9%83%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "ploughshare", "fa": "پلوس", "ur": "پلوس", "tr": "çapa demiri", "id": "pisau bajak", "bn": "প্লাউশেয়ার", "es": "arado", "fr": "soc de charrue", "de": "Pflugschar", "ru": "плуг", "zh": "犁铧"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "plowshare"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "mattock, hoe"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "die for coining, coin die, coin stamp"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "coin", "examples": [{"text": "دَار السِّكَّة", "english": "mint (for minting money)"}]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "right of coining"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "large street, high road", "examples": [{"text": "سِكَّة حَدِيد", "english": "railroad"}, {"text": "مَرَّ أَبُو نَوَّاسٍ فِي بَعْضِ سِكَكِ ٱلْبَصْرَة", "english": "Abū Nuwās passed by some streets of al-Baṣra"}]}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Likely borrowed at least partial semantics from Aramaic סִכְּתָא / ܣܶܟܬܳܐ (sekkǝṯā, “peg, nail, spike; ploughshare; coin stamp”), from Akkadian 𒄑𒆕 (sikkatum, “peg, nail, a lock or pin broach, cone, wedge, pyramid, pinnacle, plowshare”).\n\nFrom Ge'ez ሰኰት (säkʷät), ሰኮት (säkot)."}, "ipa": ["/sik.ka/", "[sækːæ]"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n20161", "headword_ar": "سِكَّةٌ", "root": "sk", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A ploughshare;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e. the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "iron thing with which the ground is ploughed;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, TA;) the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "iron appertenance of the plough."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.) Hence the trad.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA daxalati Als~ik~apu daAra qawomi A_il~aA *al~uwA", "text_ar": "مَا دَخَلَتِ السِّكَّةُ دَارَ قَوْمِ اـِلَّا ذَلُّوا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The ploughshare enters not the abode of a people,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "party, but they become abased"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; meaning, in consequence of the violence and the demands that the agriculturists experience from the ruling power. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A die,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "an engraved piece of iron,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, * Msb, K, TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "having an inscription upon it,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "with which dirhems and deenárs are stamped,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, * Msb,) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "upon which pieces of money"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daraAhim", "text_ar": "دَرَاهِم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "are struck:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sikakN", "text_ar": "سِكَكٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Msb.) ―         -b3-  And, because stamped therewith,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A coined dirhem,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "deenár;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA;) which latter is called [also] ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sikiY~N", "text_ar": "سِكِىٌّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (O, K, TA,) [in the CK"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sakiY~", "text_ar": "سَكِىّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", but it is] with kesr. (TA.)       -A2-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A row"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TariyqapN muSoTaf~apN", "text_ar": "طَرِيقَةٌ مُصْطَفَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", S, O, Msb, or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saTorN", "text_ar": "سَطْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", K, or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saTorN", "text_ar": "سَطْرٌ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maSoTaf~N", "text_ar": "مَصْطَفٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", TA)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of palm-trees."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O, Msb, K, TA.) Hence their saying, (S,) or the saying of the Prophet, (O,)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xayoru AlmaAli muhorapN maA^omuwrapN A^awo sik~apN maA^obuwrapN", "text_ar": "خَيْرُ المَالِ مُهْرَةٌ مَاْمُورَةٌ اَوْ سِكَّةٌ مَاْبُورَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, in the O"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sk~p mA^bwrp Aw mhrp mA^mwrp", "text_ar": "سكّة مابورة او مهرة مامورة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",) meaning ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The best of property is"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a prolific filly"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "or a row of palm-trees fecundated:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, TA:) or, accord. to As,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sk~p mA^bwrp", "text_ar": "سكّة مابورة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "here signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a ploughshare properly prepared"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "for ploughing"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; and, he says, the meaning is, that the best of property is a brood [of a mare] or seed-produce. (S.) [It has been suggested to me that, if"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tryqp", "text_ar": "طريقة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in the explanation above have the signification here assigned to it, the epithet"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mSTf~p", "text_ar": "مصطفّة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is redundant; and therefore that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tryqp", "text_ar": "طريقة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "alone may be the proper explanation, and may mean in this case, as it does in many others,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a tall palm-tree,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the tallest of palm-trees,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a smooth palm-tree,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a palm-tree the head of which is reached by the hand;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mSTf~p", "text_ar": "مصطفّة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "may have been added in consequence of misunderstanding, and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sTr", "text_ar": "سطر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "substituted for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tryqp", "text_ar": "طريقة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for the same reason: but I think it much more probable that the epithet has been added because"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tryqp", "text_ar": "طريقة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is ambiguous; and this is confirmed by what here follows.] ―         -b2-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zuqaAq", "text_ar": "زُقَاق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "street"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (S, O, * Msb:) or [rather]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a wide"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zuqaAq", "text_ar": "زُقَاق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Msb:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "an even road,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA,) [or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "street,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of such as are termed"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aziq~ap", "text_ar": "اَزِقَّة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zuqaAq", "text_ar": "زُقَاق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (TA:) so called because the houses therein form a row or rows [on either side]; (O, TA;) being likened to a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sik~ap", "text_ar": "سِكَّة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of palm-trees: (TA:) [in the present day, often applied to"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a highway,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and to"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "any road:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sikakN", "text_ar": "سِكَكٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[as above]: (O:) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sakaAy^iku", "text_ar": "سَكَايِكُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "syn. with"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sikakN", "text_ar": "سِكَكٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as meaning]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aziq~apN", "text_ar": "اَزِقَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) ―         -b3-  [Hence also, app., one says,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AijoEali", "text_ar": "اِجْعَلِ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^amora sik~apF waAHidapF", "text_ar": "الاَمْرَ سِكَّةً وَاحِدَةً"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Make thou the affair,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "case,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "uniform,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "one uniform thing."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Fr, TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bA^j", "text_ar": "باج"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) ―         -b4-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^axa*a AlA^amora bisik~atihi", "text_ar": "اَخَذَ الاَمْرَ بِسِكَّتِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^adorakahu", "text_ar": "اَدْرَكَهُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bisik~atihi", "text_ar": "بِسِكَّتِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (TA,) (assumed tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He took the thing,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he attained it, in its proper way,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "when it was possible."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA.) ―         -b5-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fulaAnN SaEobu Alsik~api", "text_ar": "فُلَانٌ صَعْبُ السِكَّةِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Such a one will not remain quiet,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "still,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "steady, by reason of hastiness of temper."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Ibn- 'Abbád, Z, O, TA.)       -A3-  Also The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "house"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "station"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bariyd", "text_ar": "بَرِيد"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "messenger that journeys on a beast of the post,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "messengers on beasts of the post:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "it is likewise called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sik~apu Albariydi", "text_ar": "سِكَّةُ البَرِيدِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bariydN", "text_ar": "بَرِيدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aSoHaAbu Als~ikaki", "text_ar": "اَصْحَابُ السِّكَكِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", occurring in a letter of 'Omar Ibn-'Abd-El-'Azeez, means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "burud", "text_ar": "بُرُد"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "messengers on beasts of the post"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "who are stationed there to be sent on affairs of importance."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh.)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sik~apu", "text_ar": "سِكَّةُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Albariydi", "text_ar": "البَرِيدِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is well known [as having the meaning assigned to it above: and also as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The space,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "distance, between each station of the messengers above mentioned and the station next to it:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "see, again,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bariydN", "text_ar": "بَرِيدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Ibn-'Abbád, O.)"}], "source_refs": ["TA", "K", "O", "S", "Msb"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}